{"kind": "section", "id": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/platforms.md#overview", "page_url": "https://code.claude.com/docs/en/platforms.md", "anchor": "overview", "breadcrumb": "Platforms and integrations > Overview", "level": 2, "position": 0, "text": "> Choose where to run Claude Code and what to connect it to. Compare the CLI, Desktop, VS Code, JetBrains, web, mobile, and integrations like Chrome, Slack, and CI/CD.\n\nClaude Code runs the same underlying engine everywhere, but each surface is tuned for a different way of working. This page helps you pick the right platform for your workflow and connect the tools you already use.", "synthesized": false, "parent_section_id": null, "external_links": []}
